{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"changed"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This affects sorting and filtering."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that calls to this method must be in sync with the data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"used for the sorting and filtering functions. For instance, if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the list is mirroring some external data set, and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"two"}]},{"type":"text","text":" children"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"changed in the external data set when you call"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gtk_flow_box_child_changed()"},{"type":"text","text":" on the first child, the sort function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"must only read the new data for the first of the two changed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"children, otherwise the resorting of the children will be wrong."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This generally means that if you donâ€™t fully control the data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"model, you have to duplicate the data that affects the sorting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and filtering functions into the widgets themselves."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Another alternative is to call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.FlowBox.invalidate_sort"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on any model change, but that is more expensive."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gtk\/flowboxchildprotocol\/changed()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/FlowBoxChildProtocol\/changed()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Marks "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"child"},{"type":"text","text":" as changed, causing any state that depends on this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to be updated."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"changed()","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"changed"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3Gtk20FlowBoxChildProtocolPAAE7changedyyF","extendedModule":"Gtk","modules":[{"name":"Gtk"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/FlowBoxChildProtocol"]]},"references":{"doc://Gtk/documentation/Gtk/FlowBoxChildProtocol":{"role":"symbol","title":"FlowBoxChildProtocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"FlowBoxChildProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkFlowBoxChild"},{"type":"text","text":" is the kind of widget that can be added to a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkFlowBox"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/FlowBoxChildProtocol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"FlowBoxChildProtocol"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gtk\/flowboxchildprotocol"},"doc://Gtk/documentation/Gtk":{"role":"collection","title":"Gtk","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gtk"},"doc://Gtk/documentation/Gtk/FlowBoxChildProtocol/changed()":{"role":"symbol","title":"changed()","fragments":[{"kind":"ke